<TITLE> Coach lauds Chanderpaul for leading record bid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MANCHESTER, June 11 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - West Indies coach David Moore paid tribute to Shivnarine Chanderpaul after the experienced batsman kept the side in the highest run chase in test history, against England in the third test on Sunday. "Teams that under-estimate Chanderpaul do so at their own peril because he is a tremendous cricketer," Moore said. "Chanderpaul is under-estimated and under-rated, he is a world-class player." The tourists, 1-0 down in the four-match series and chasing 455 to win, will resume at Old Trafford on Monday on 301 for five with Guyanan Chanderpaul 81 not out and wicketkeeper Denesh Ramdin on 26. The record score to win a test match batting in the fourth innings is the 418 that West Indies scored against world champions Australia in 2003 in Antigua. "This is a performance we should be seeing from the West Indies every tim
